<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="99" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1461,2026]" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,326,1497,1522]" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Etymology</emphasis>
. “ 
<emphasis box="[361,475,1498,1521]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Pepoapua</emphasis>
” (pronounced /pepəɑpuːɑ/), a compound of two words from the native South American Tupi-Guarani language. “ 
<taxonomicName authority="P.Miller, 1754" authorityName="P.Miller" authorityYear="1754" box="[553,611,1534,1557]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Cucurbitaceae" genus="Pepo" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cucurbitales" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[553,611,1534,1557]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Pepó</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” means wing and “apu’a” means short. Name given in allusion to the fact that the species here described present short wings.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="99" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1461,2026]" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,314,1605,1630]" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. This new genus is characterized by the combination of the following characters: (i) males and females with morphologically similar tegmina (
<figureCitation box="[708,790,1641,1666]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1678,1700]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,664,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,663,1656]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., male holotype (habitus). A—dorsal view; B—lateral view; C—ventral view; D—head and pronotum, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892641/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
A, B, D; 3A and 5A, B, D); (ii) tegmina reduced, not reaching half of the second abdominal segment (
<figureCitation box="[694,761,1677,1702]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1678,1700]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,664,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,663,1656]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., male holotype (habitus). A—dorsal view; B—lateral view; C—ventral view; D—head and pronotum, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892641/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A, B, D); (iii) dorsal field of the tegmina with parallel veins, without stridulatory vein or any specialized area for sound production (
<figureCitation box="[960,1027,1713,1738]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1354,1376]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., paratype (A – B) and male holotype (C – I). A— dorsal view of right tegmen; B—detail of right tegmen, dorsal view; C—dorsal spurs of hind tibia; D—detail of proximo-dorsal inner spur of tibia of the third pair of legs (non-specialized); E—ventro-apical inner and outer spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs (arrows); F—outer apical spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: o. s: outer superior, o. m: outer median, o. v: outer ventral; G—apical inner spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: i. s: inner superior, i. m: inner median, i. v: inner ventral; H—supranal plate; Isubgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892643/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
A); (iv) tibia of the first pair of legs without tympanum; (v) tibia of the third pair of legs with seven dorsal spurs, four inner and three outer (
<figureCitation box="[1334,1401,1749,1774]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1354,1376]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., paratype (A – B) and male holotype (C – I). A— dorsal view of right tegmen; B—detail of right tegmen, dorsal view; C—dorsal spurs of hind tibia; D—detail of proximo-dorsal inner spur of tibia of the third pair of legs (non-specialized); E—ventro-apical inner and outer spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs (arrows); F—outer apical spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: o. s: outer superior, o. m: outer median, o. v: outer ventral; G—apical inner spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: i. s: inner superior, i. m: inner median, i. v: inner ventral; H—supranal plate; Isubgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892643/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C), the proximo-dorsal inner spur reduced in size (
<figureCitation box="[676,742,1785,1810]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1354,1376]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., paratype (A – B) and male holotype (C – I). A— dorsal view of right tegmen; B—detail of right tegmen, dorsal view; C—dorsal spurs of hind tibia; D—detail of proximo-dorsal inner spur of tibia of the third pair of legs (non-specialized); E—ventro-apical inner and outer spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs (arrows); F—outer apical spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: o. s: outer superior, o. m: outer median, o. v: outer ventral; G—apical inner spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: i. s: inner superior, i. m: inner median, i. v: inner ventral; H—supranal plate; Isubgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892643/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C, D) and the disto-dorsal inner spur without glandular aspect (
<figureCitation box="[159,230,1821,1846]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1354,1376]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., paratype (A – B) and male holotype (C – I). A— dorsal view of right tegmen; B—detail of right tegmen, dorsal view; C—dorsal spurs of hind tibia; D—detail of proximo-dorsal inner spur of tibia of the third pair of legs (non-specialized); E—ventro-apical inner and outer spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs (arrows); F—outer apical spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: o. s: outer superior, o. m: outer median, o. v: outer ventral; G—apical inner spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: i. s: inner superior, i. m: inner median, i. v: inner ventral; H—supranal plate; Isubgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892643/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C); (vi) ovipositor with distal portion of the dorsal and ventral valves serrated (
<figureCitation box="[1178,1248,1821,1846]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1864,1886]" captionTargetBox="[169,1419,194,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[168,1419,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., paratype female. A—habitus in dorsal view; B—habitus in lateral view; C—habitus ventral view; D—head and pronotum, in lateral view; E—supranal plate; F—subgenital plate; G—ovipositor, in lateral view; H—ovipositor, in ventral view; I—detail of distal portion of ovipositor." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892647/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
G–I); (vii) male genitalia without evident bristles or sensillas (
<figureCitation box="[687,760,1857,1882]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1893,1915]" captionTargetBox="[284,1302,723,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[284,1302,723,1872]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., genitalia of male paratype. A — Photograph in ventral view; B — Photograph in dorsal view; C — Photograph in lateral view; D — Illustration in ventral view; E — Illustration in dorsal view; F — Illustration in lateral view. Abbreviations: ps. a. l—pseudepiphallic apical lobe; ps. m. l—pseudepiphallic median lobe; ps. ppseudepiphallic parameres; ps. sc—pseudepiphallic sclerite; ec. f—ectophallic fold; v. v—ventral valve; end. sc—endophallic sclerite; a. g—accessory gland." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892645/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); (viii) pseudepiphallic median lobe presenting apical and ventral projections (
<figureCitation box="[375,443,1893,1918]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1893,1915]" captionTargetBox="[284,1302,723,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[284,1302,723,1872]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., genitalia of male paratype. A — Photograph in ventral view; B — Photograph in dorsal view; C — Photograph in lateral view; D — Illustration in ventral view; E — Illustration in dorsal view; F — Illustration in lateral view. Abbreviations: ps. a. l—pseudepiphallic apical lobe; ps. m. l—pseudepiphallic median lobe; ps. ppseudepiphallic parameres; ps. sc—pseudepiphallic sclerite; ec. f—ectophallic fold; v. v—ventral valve; end. sc—endophallic sclerite; a. g—accessory gland." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892645/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
A, C, D, F).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1436,1461,2026]" lastBlockId="4.[151,1437,151,608]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="100" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,1929,1954]" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Description</emphasis>
. Small size (Ẽ 
<quantity box="[499,561,1929,1954]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="99" unit="mm" value="6.0">6mm</quantity>
). Head as wide as pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[889,956,1929,1954]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1678,1700]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,664,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,663,1656]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., male holotype (habitus). A—dorsal view; B—lateral view; C—ventral view; D—head and pronotum, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892641/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A), covered by long semi-erect dark brown bristles on fastigium, vertex and occiput; presence of thin bristles covering its entire length; black and prominent eyes (
<figureCitation box="[217,285,2001,2026]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1678,1700]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,664,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,663,1656]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., male holotype (habitus). A—dorsal view; B—lateral view; C—ventral view; D—head and pronotum, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892641/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="99">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A-D); three ocelli present; 5-segmented maxillary palps, with the third being larger than the first and second, but smaller than the fourth and fifth palpomere (
<figureCitation box="[802,871,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1678,1700]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,664,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,663,1656]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., male holotype (habitus). A—dorsal view; B—lateral view; C—ventral view; D—head and pronotum, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892641/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D); fifth palpomere with rounded apex (
<figureCitation box="[1331,1400,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1678,1700]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,664,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,663,1656]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., male holotype (habitus). A—dorsal view; B—lateral view; C—ventral view; D—head and pronotum, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892641/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
D). Pronotum wider than long, covered with long and fine bristles of dark brown coloration; anterior and posterior edges with a row of long dark brown bristles (
<figureCitation box="[671,738,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1678,1700]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,664,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,663,1656]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., male holotype (habitus). A—dorsal view; B—lateral view; C—ventral view; D—head and pronotum, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892641/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
A, B, D); lateral lobes as in 
<figureCitation box="[1055,1151,223,248]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1678,1700]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,664,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,663,1656]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., male holotype (habitus). A—dorsal view; B—lateral view; C—ventral view; D—head and pronotum, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892641/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Figure 2</figureCitation>
D; tegmina reduced, with parallel veins and without specialization (
<figureCitation box="[620,696,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1678,1700]" captionTargetBox="[168,1419,664,1656]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[168,1419,663,1656]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 2. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., male holotype (habitus). A—dorsal view; B—lateral view; C—ventral view; D—head and pronotum, lateral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892641/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Figs. 2</figureCitation>
A and 3A); posterior wings absent; tympanum absent; tibia of the first pair of legs with an apical spur; tibia of the second pair of legs with two apical spurs; tibia of the third pair of legs with seven dorsal spurs, being four inner and three outer (
<figureCitation box="[862,929,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1354,1376]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., paratype (A – B) and male holotype (C – I). A— dorsal view of right tegmen; B—detail of right tegmen, dorsal view; C—dorsal spurs of hind tibia; D—detail of proximo-dorsal inner spur of tibia of the third pair of legs (non-specialized); E—ventro-apical inner and outer spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs (arrows); F—outer apical spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: o. s: outer superior, o. m: outer median, o. v: outer ventral; G—apical inner spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: i. s: inner superior, i. m: inner median, i. v: inner ventral; H—supranal plate; Isubgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892643/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
C), the proximo-dorsal inner spur reduced in size (
<figureCitation box="[213,281,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1354,1376]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., paratype (A – B) and male holotype (C – I). A— dorsal view of right tegmen; B—detail of right tegmen, dorsal view; C—dorsal spurs of hind tibia; D—detail of proximo-dorsal inner spur of tibia of the third pair of legs (non-specialized); E—ventro-apical inner and outer spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs (arrows); F—outer apical spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: o. s: outer superior, o. m: outer median, o. v: outer ventral; G—apical inner spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: i. s: inner superior, i. m: inner median, i. v: inner ventral; H—supranal plate; Isubgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892643/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
D) and the disto-dorsal inner spur without glandular aspect (non-specialized) (
<figureCitation box="[1189,1259,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1354,1376]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., paratype (A – B) and male holotype (C – I). A— dorsal view of right tegmen; B—detail of right tegmen, dorsal view; C—dorsal spurs of hind tibia; D—detail of proximo-dorsal inner spur of tibia of the third pair of legs (non-specialized); E—ventro-apical inner and outer spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs (arrows); F—outer apical spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: o. s: outer superior, o. m: outer median, o. v: outer ventral; G—apical inner spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: i. s: inner superior, i. m: inner median, i. v: inner ventral; H—supranal plate; Isubgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892643/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
