<figureCitation box="[855,923,439,464]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="5.[151,250,1354,1376]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetId="figure@5.[151,1436,193,1333]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 3. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., paratype (A – B) and male holotype (C – I). A— dorsal view of right tegmen; B—detail of right tegmen, dorsal view; C—dorsal spurs of hind tibia; D—detail of proximo-dorsal inner spur of tibia of the third pair of legs (non-specialized); E—ventro-apical inner and outer spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs (arrows); F—outer apical spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: o. s: outer superior, o. m: outer median, o. v: outer ventral; G—apical inner spurs of the tibia of the third pair of legs: i. s: inner superior, i. m: inner median, i. v: inner ventral; H—supranal plate; Isubgenital plate." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892643/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
G, &quot;i.s&quot;). Male genitalia: bristles or sensillas absent (
<figureCitation box="[245,322,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1893,1915]" captionTargetBox="[284,1302,723,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[284,1302,723,1872]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., genitalia of male paratype. A — Photograph in ventral view; B — Photograph in dorsal view; C — Photograph in lateral view; D — Illustration in ventral view; E — Illustration in dorsal view; F — Illustration in lateral view. Abbreviations: ps. a. l—pseudepiphallic apical lobe; ps. m. l—pseudepiphallic median lobe; ps. ppseudepiphallic parameres; ps. sc—pseudepiphallic sclerite; ec. f—ectophallic fold; v. v—ventral valve; end. sc—endophallic sclerite; a. g—accessory gland." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892645/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); pseudepiphallic median lobe presenting apical and ventral projections (
<figureCitation box="[1206,1281,476,501]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1893,1915]" captionTargetBox="[284,1302,723,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[284,1302,723,1872]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., genitalia of male paratype. A — Photograph in ventral view; B — Photograph in dorsal view; C — Photograph in lateral view; D — Illustration in ventral view; E — Illustration in dorsal view; F — Illustration in lateral view. Abbreviations: ps. a. l—pseudepiphallic apical lobe; ps. m. l—pseudepiphallic median lobe; ps. ppseudepiphallic parameres; ps. sc—pseudepiphallic sclerite; ec. f—ectophallic fold; v. v—ventral valve; end. sc—endophallic sclerite; a. g—accessory gland." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892645/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
A, C, D, F); endophallus divided in three sclerites, being one central and two laterals (
<figureCitation box="[1047,1121,511,536]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1893,1915]" captionTargetBox="[284,1302,723,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[284,1302,723,1872]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., genitalia of male paratype. A — Photograph in ventral view; B — Photograph in dorsal view; C — Photograph in lateral view; D — Illustration in ventral view; E — Illustration in dorsal view; F — Illustration in lateral view. Abbreviations: ps. a. l—pseudepiphallic apical lobe; ps. m. l—pseudepiphallic median lobe; ps. ppseudepiphallic parameres; ps. sc—pseudepiphallic sclerite; ec. f—ectophallic fold; v. v—ventral valve; end. sc—endophallic sclerite; a. g—accessory gland." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892645/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
A, D); rami fusioned with pseudepiphallus (
<figureCitation box="[352,424,548,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="6.[151,250,1893,1915]" captionTargetBox="[284,1302,723,1872]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[284,1302,723,1872]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="FIGURE 4. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., genitalia of male paratype. A — Photograph in ventral view; B — Photograph in dorsal view; C — Photograph in lateral view; D — Illustration in ventral view; E — Illustration in dorsal view; F — Illustration in lateral view. Abbreviations: ps. a. l—pseudepiphallic apical lobe; ps. m. l—pseudepiphallic median lobe; ps. ppseudepiphallic parameres; ps. sc—pseudepiphallic sclerite; ec. f—ectophallic fold; v. v—ventral valve; end. sc—endophallic sclerite; a. g—accessory gland." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892645/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
A, C, D, F). Ovipositor flattened laterally, dorsal and ventral valves serrated in distal portions (
<figureCitation box="[258,323,583,608]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="7.[151,250,1864,1886]" captionTargetBox="[169,1419,194,1842]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[168,1419,193,1843]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 5. Pepoapua cariacica Jesus &amp; Pereira n. sp., paratype female. A—habitus in dorsal view; B—habitus in lateral view; C—habitus ventral view; D—head and pronotum, in lateral view; E—supranal plate; F—subgenital plate; G—ovipositor, in lateral view; H—ovipositor, in ventral view; I—detail of distal portion of ovipositor." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/892647/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="100">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
G–I).
